The paper deals with a problem of anomaly detection using nonparametric methods based on kernel mean embedding. This is a common topic in machine learning and statistics, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves statistical testing and information theory, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of kernel methods and nonparametric techniques further suggests that the paper may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ML (Machine Learning) as well.
